  "line": 1214,
  "cap": "OS_COMMAND",
  "endpoint": "<cli:scan --since-ref>",
  "rationale": "collect_changed_files builds `git -C <ws> diff --name-only --diff-filter=AMR {ref_name}...HEAD` and feeds {ref_name} (operator's --since-ref CLI value) verbatim into .arg(format!(\"{ref_name}...HEAD\")). No `--` end-of-options separator precedes the ref. Refs that start with a dash are parsed by git as options: `--since-ref='--output=/tmp/pwn'` becomes argv `--output=/tmp/pwn...HEAD`, which git diff accepts as --output=<path>, writing the diff to an attacker-chosen path — arbitrary file write as the daemon uid. Similarly `--upload-pack=...` style flags reroute helper execution. Command::new is shell-free so no metacharacter injection, but git's own option parsing is the injection surface. Static pass missed because the value never touches `sh -c` and the format! looks like a ref-spec, not an option.",
  "suggested_payload_hint": "nyx-agent scan --since-ref='--output=/Users/<op>/.ssh/authorized_keys' → git writes diff body into the target file; or '--upload-pack=/tmp/payload' to coerce helper exec on a fetch path."
