es log access; this one needs only tcpdump on the segment). Also: line 50 says `Never run a public daemon in --headless` but the binary has no startup-time guard that refuses `--headless --listen <non-loopback>` (verified: main.rs has no precondition coupling those flags). The pass-11 `<api:/api/v1/*>` AUTH_BYPASS row covers the code path; this row covers the doc trust boundary that *invites* operators into the foot-gun and contradicts itself two lines apart (line 48 says it is OK with TLS that does not exist, line 50 says do not, with no enforcement). Static pass missed because (a) Markdown is not on the input list, (b) the bug is the absence of a precondition in the binary AND the absence of a 'TLS not built in — terminate at a reverse proxy' note in the docs; neither is a tainted-flow signature. Fix: (1) edit cli.md:48 to drop the bare-binary-on-0.0.0.0 recipe; instead document the reverse-proxy pattern explicitly: `nyx-agent serve --listen 127.0.0.1:8765` behind nginx/caddy with TLS, plus a Host-header allowlist (also closes the prior DNS_REBIND row). (2) Add a startup-time refusal in main.rs serve(): if listen_addr is non-loopback AND no `i_understand_tls_terminator_in_front=true` config bit is set, log a stderr warning and (in debug builds) refuse to bind. (3) Add a startup-time refusal for `--headless && listen_addr != 127.0.0.1` — that pair is the unauthenticated-public-daemon shape the doc warns against in prose but does not enforce in code.",
