  "rationale": "`resolve_run_project` (main.rs:1088-1109) reads `selected.first().project_id`, looks it up via `store.projects().get(...)`, and on `None` *silently substitutes the default project* via `ensure_default`. Two distinct integrity gaps fall out: (1) **Cross-project event mislabelling.** The dispatcher constructs `DispatcherView { project_id: project.id.as_str().to_string() }` from the resolved project and tags every per-repo event (`RepoStarted`, `RepoStaticDone`, `RepoFailed`, `RepoFinished`) with that single value (run/mod.rs:307, 405, 419, 432, 444, 457). The comment at main.rs:451 says 'All `selected` repos are *expected* to share the same `project_id`' — expectation, not enforcement. drive_scan never validates the invariant. If `selected` contains repos from two projects (CLI flag `nyx-agent scan repo1 repo2` where the two repos belong to different projects in the DB), every event for repo2 still carries project1's id, while `upsert_repo_record` (main.rs:1066) writes each repo's true project_id into the DB and `state_dir.project_repos(repo.project_id.as_str())` (main.rs:460) writes the workspace under each repo's real project dir. Net: events lie about repo ownership relative to durable state — a UI subscriber listening on `project_id == X` sees repo Y stream past even though Y was scanned as part of project Z's run, and the DB+filesystem disagree with the event bus. The hard part: `RunStarted` carries `project_id = project.id` but `repos: Vec<String>` includes names from foreign projects; a downstream chain-validation consumer that grants access to AgentEvents for a project leaks per-repo metadata (repo names, finding bodies, callgraph nodes) across project boundaries. (2) **Default-project substitution on missing id.** If `selected.first().project_id` resolves to a row that has been deleted between `repos.select` and `resolve_run_project` (race; or DB editor cleanup), the `ensure_default` fallback replaces it with `default-project` — but the per-repo `repo.project_id` is still the deleted id, so `state_dir.project_repos(repo.project_id.as_str())` writes the workspace into the dangling project dir, `upsert_repo_record` writes the deleted project_id into the FK column (FK constraint violation iff the row really is gone; otherwise silent data inconsistency), and ProjectStarted/ProjectFinished envelope the run with the *wrong* project_id. The static pass misses this because the bug is the *absence* of `if !selected.iter().all(|r| r.project_id == first) { return Err }` and `if rec.is_none() { return Err }` — there is no tainted-flow sink to alarm on. Distinct from any prior sentinel row: pre-Phase-4 there was no project concept; the substitution and missing invariant check are net-new this session. Fix: (a) reject mixed-project `selected` at the top of `drive_scan` with `ApiError::BadRequest(\"all repos in a scan must share project_id\")`. (b) Change `resolve_run_project` to return `ApiError::NotFound` when the project id is missing — never fall back to default; the default project should only be materialised by the explicit bootstrap path (`ensure_default` from migrations), not laundered through a run. (c) Plumb `project_id` per `RepoStarted/RepoFinished` from `repo.project_id` (the durable truth) rather than `view.project_id` (the resolved-once value), or assert equality at emission.",
  "suggested_payload_hint": "(a) mixed-project repro: seed two projects A and B, attach repo `alpha` to A and `beta` to B, then `nyx-agent scan alpha beta` — capture the JSONL event stream via `--events-file`; grep for `RepoStarted` and `RepoFinished` rows and observe both rows carry `project_id: A` while `state.sqlite \"SELECT name, project_id FROM repos\"` shows `alpha=A, beta=B`. (b) deletion-race repro: `sqlite3 state.sqlite \"BEGIN; SELECT * FROM repos WHERE name='alpha';\"` from one shell to hold a transaction, in a second shell `DELETE FROM projects WHERE id = (SELECT project_id FROM repos WHERE name='alpha')` (the FK is ON DELETE RESTRICT today? if so this won't fire; if it's CASCADE the repo row disappears too — either way the run sees inconsistent state); then `nyx-agent scan alpha` and observe `ProjectStarted { project_id: default-project }` even though the repo row was attached elsewhere. Fix-validation regression: after the proposed guards, a mixed-project CLI invocation should exit 1 with `error: repos span multiple projects; run a scan per project` *before* `dispatch_project` is called."
}

