  "rationale": "`resolve_run_project` decodes the project's stored env_config blob with `r.env_config_json.as_deref().and_then(|s| serde_json::from_str(s).ok())` — the `.ok()` discards every parse error and returns `None`. The downstream consumers (Phase-3 env-builder merge, Phase-18 sandbox lane env restriction) interpret `env_config: None` as 'no project env policy' and run with the *default permissive* env. So a corrupted or truncated env_config JSON in the `projects` row — whether from a partial write (db on full disk), a botched migration, a hand-edit, or future deserialisation drift between schema versions — silently demotes the project from 'restricted env' to 'open env' on the next scan. Concrete impact path: an operator configures `env_config_json = '{\"allow\":[\"PATH\",\"HOME\"]}'` to keep secrets out of subprocess env, a later schema-evolution PR (Phase 6+) renames `allow` to `allowlist` and the un-migrated row no longer parses as the new schema — this code silently treats it as no restriction, the next dispatch_project hands the unrestricted env to the sandbox lane, and `git clone`-driven hooks (ext::, post-clone) see the daemon's full env (HOME, AWS_*, GITHUB_TOKEN, NYX_LICENSE_KEY) on stdout via the prior `git ext::` OS_COMMAND row. The static pass missed this because `.ok()` on a Result is not in any tainted-sink rule; the bug is a fail-open default. Distinct from the pass-1 CRED_EXPOSURE TraceLayer row (that one leaks via logs; this one leaks via subprocess env after silent demotion). Distinct from the prior CONFIG_TAMPER rows on the YAML/TOML side (those rows targeted operator-facing config files, not the SQLite-backed project record). Fix: (a) propagate the parse error — return `StoreError::CorruptEnvConfig { project_id, source }` rather than swallowing it; the caller should refuse the scan with `error: project <id> has unparseable env_config; refusing to run with default-permissive env`. (b) At minimum, log the parse failure at WARN with the project id and the first error kind. (c) Cover with a unit test that `env_config_json: \"{garbage\"` returns an error rather than `Some(Project { env_config: None, .. })`.",
  "suggested_payload_hint": "repro: `sqlite3 state.sqlite \"UPDATE projects SET env_config_json = '{not valid' WHERE id = 'default-project';\"` then `nyx-agent scan alpha --verbose` — the run starts cleanly with no warning, but a Phase-18 sandbox lane subscribe sees `Project { env_config: None }` rather than a restriction. Adjacent regression: after the fix, the same UPDATE should make `nyx-agent scan alpha` exit 1 with the corruption error, *before* dispatch_project mints a ProjectStarted event. Schema-drift variant: bump the env_config schema version in a follow-up PR and run an old row through the new parser — same silent demotion."
}

