record_exploration_finding
{
  "path": "crates/nyx-agent-ai/src/runtime.rs",
  "line": 138,
  "cap": "BUDGET_BYPASS",
  "rationale": "Budget cap enforcement is racy across concurrent AI calls. AnthropicSdkAdapter::one_shot (anthropic.rs:175-189, 270-292) does check-then-act: read `current_spend`, compare to `cap`, dispatch HTTP, then `add_spend`. `BudgetTracker::add_spend` (runtime.rs:135-149) is NOT atomic with the pre-call read — it only locks long enough to mutate one Row's `spent_usd_micros`. Two `one_shot` calls (or one_shot + agent_loop, since they share the same Budget bucket for ExplorationScope.run_id) racing for the same (run_id, kind) can each observe `spent_before <= cap`, each issue a $9 call against a $10 cap, then each post-call add lands the row at $18 — past the cap, no halt. The hard-cap promise in tasks/exploration.rs:271-275 (DEFAULT_EXPLORATION_RUN_CAP_USD_MICROS = $10) is therefore a best-effort ceiling, not an enforced one. Static pass misses because the per-call sequence (read, compare, add) is locally correct — the bug only appears when two adapter instances or two tokio tasks run simultaneously, which the unit tests do not exercise (every existing test awaits one call before issuing the next).",
  "suggested_payload_hint": "Stand up two AnthropicSdkAdapter instances sharing one Arc<InMemoryBudgetTracker>, set_cap(run, OneShot, 100), pre-load spent=0, then `tokio::join!(a.one_shot(...), b.one_shot(...))` with each wiremock response priced at 80 micros. Both calls pass the `spent_before > cap` gate (each reads 0), both POST, both add_spend — final tracker.spent() = 160 > cap = 100 with no BudgetExceeded raised. Fix: collapse pre-check + add into one atomic `try_add_spend(cap)` that returns BudgetExceeded when the new total would exceed cap, executed before the HTTP call (and refunded if the call fails), or guard the (read,post) window with a per-(run_id,kind) mutex."
}

